{"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"atexit"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"text":"func","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"GVoidFunc","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@GVoidFunc"},{"text":"?)","kind":"text"}],"languages":["swift"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"level":2,"text":"Discussion","anchor":"discussion","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Since GLib 2.8.2, on Windows "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_atexit()"},{"type":"text","text":" actually is a preprocessor"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"macro that maps to a call to the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"atexit()"},{"type":"text","text":" function in the C"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"library. This means that in case the code that calls "},{"code":"g_atexit()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":",","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"i.e. "},{"code":"atexit()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", is in a DLL, the function will be called when the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"DLL is detached from the program. This typically makes more sense"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"than that the function is called when the GLib DLL is detached,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"which happened earlier when "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_atexit()"},{"type":"text","text":" was a function in the GLib"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"DLL.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The behaviour of "},{"code":"atexit()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" in the context of dynamically loaded","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"modules is not formally specified and varies wildly.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"On POSIX systems, calling "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_atexit()"},{"text":" (or ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"atexit()"},{"type":"text","text":") in a dynamically"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"loaded module which is unloaded before the program terminates might"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"well cause a crash at program exit."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Some POSIX systems implement "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"atexit()"},{"text":" like Windows, and have each","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"dynamically loaded module maintain an own atexit chain that is","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"called when the module is unloaded.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"On other POSIX systems, before a dynamically loaded module is"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"unloaded, the registered atexit functions (if any) residing in that","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"module are called, regardless where the code that registered them"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"resided. This is presumably the most robust approach."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"As can be seen from the above, for portability it’s best to avoid"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"calling "},{"code":"g_atexit()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" (or ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"atexit()"},{"type":"text","text":") except in the main executable of a"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"program.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"atexit is deprecated:","type":"text"}]},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"It is best to avoid g_atexit().","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"kind":"content"}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/atexit(func:)","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"metadata":{"title":"atexit(func:)","modules":[{"name":"GLib"}],"symbolKind":"func","roleHeading":"Function","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"atexit","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"func"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"GVoidFunc","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@GVoidFunc"},{"text":"?)","kind":"text"}],"platforms":[],"role":"symbol","externalID":"s:4GLib6atexit4funcyyyXCSg_tF"},"kind":"symbol","variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/atexit(func:)"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib"]]},"sections":[],"abstract":[{"text":"Specifies a function to be called at normal program termination.","type":"text"}],"references":{"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/atexit(func:)":{"url":"\/documentation\/glib\/atexit(func:)","kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"text":"Specifies a function to be called at normal program termination.","type":"text"}],"title":"atexit(func:)","deprecated":true,"role":"symbol","type":"topic","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"atexit","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@GVoidFunc","text":"GVoidFunc","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":"?)","kind":"text"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/atexit(func:)"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib","title":"GLib","kind":"symbol","role":"collection","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/glib","abstract":[]}}}